    kind: no-op
    message: No changes — scanner crate already matches the prompt; cargo test green.
    reasoning: Prompt diff was empty (NO CHANGES). Agent reports the existing scanner/src/lib.rs and scanner/Cargo.toml already implement the described behavior, and `cargo test -p scanner` passes 15/15. No requirement was unmet, so no edits were produced.
  - promptLines:
      - 33
      - 34
    kind: ambiguity
    message: "'inclusive-in-spirit span' is vague and conflicts with the exclusive end columns used everywhere else."
    reasoning: Line 34 calls Span 'inclusive-in-spirit', but every worked span computes the end column as start + UTF-16 length (e.g. module value auth/session (1,8)-(1,20), a 12-unit value), which is an exclusive/past-the-end column. The 'inclusive' wording contradicts the actual half-open convention and would confuse anyone implementing containment tests. find_target_at_position (line 128) then treats both ends as inclusive, making the semantics inconsistent across the doc.
    suggestion: "State the exact convention: end.character is the column just past the last UTF-16 unit of the token (half-open on character), and clarify that containment in find_target_at_position treats that end as inclusive."
